# Project context (Thailand Panties)

**Before making non-trivial changes**, read **`AGENTS.md`** at the repo root and treat it as the source of truth.

## Production setup (two repos, no monorepo)

| Repo | What | Deploy target |
|------|------|---------------|
| **`Desktop/frontend`** → `kyleroofaff/frontend` | React + Vite SPA | Docker → nginx on Droplet (port 80) |
| **`Desktop/backend`** → `kyleroofaff/backend` | Express API (port 4000) | Docker → node on Droplet |

**`Desktop/tp`** (`kyleroofaff/thp`) is **test/sandbox only** — do not deploy from it, do not sync to it.

## Dev

- Frontend: `npm run dev` → Vite :5173, proxies `/api` → `:4000`
- Backend: `npm run dev` → Express :4000 with `--watch`
- Production API: `https://api.thailandpanties.com` (resolved by `VITE_API_BASE_URL` or host fallback in `site.jsx`)

## Code hotspots

- `src/site.jsx` — main app shell, routing, API client
- `src/pages/DashboardPages.jsx` — dashboard surfaces
- `vite.config.js` — dev proxy, build stamp plugin
- `nginx.conf` — SPA cache rules

## Rules

- **Persist facts in-repo**: update `AGENTS.md` (or this rule) when setup changes — do not rely on chat memory.
- **Access**: full workspace + git history. No cloud dashboards, SSH, or secrets unless user provides them.
- When user says "deploy" or "production," confirm against `AGENTS.md` and remind them `git push` alone does not update production unless the Droplet rebuilds.
